               <location>
                  <geo>14.205083 39.4992</geo>
                  <height unit="m">2700.0</height>
               </location>
               <note>
                  <date type="foundation" notBefore="1400" notAfter="1500">1400-1500</date>
                  <desc type="foundation">According to local tradition, the foundation took place during the time of King <persName ref="PRS1854Amdase">King ʿĀmda Ṣǝyon I</persName> (r. <date>1314-1334</date>).</desc>
                  <ab type="history">Dabr. Formerly, the church could have a different name, cp. GSM-002, Zag(g)ābo/Zag(g)ābu Māryām. Currently, the site accomodates two churches. 
                     The recent (late <date>19th or 20th cent.?</date>), rectangular church dedicated to <ref type="authFile" corresp="CovenantMercy">Kidāna Mǝḥrat</ref> stands below, 
                     and the old rock-hewn church dedicated to St. <persName ref="PRS6819Mary" type="tabot">Mary</persName> is located above, cut in the rock. 
                     Many holes and small caves can be seen in the vertical rock around its entrance, formerly used as burials (in a few of them wooden caffins could still be seen) or dwellings of the monks.&#xD;
</ab>
                  <ab type="description">
                     <figure>
                        <graphic url="Sites/GMS.tif">
                           <desc>The church photographed by Denis Nosnitsin during the Ethio-SPaRe project.</desc>
                        </graphic>
                     </figure>
                     18 Mss., objects photographed: <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgms001">GMS-001</ref> "The Rite of the Holy Week"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgms002">GMS-002</ref> "Four Gospels"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgms003">GMS-003</ref> "The Book of the Funeral Rite"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgms004">GMS-004</ref> "Missal"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgms005">GMS-005</ref> "Miracles of Jesus"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgms006">GMS-006</ref> "Synaxarion (March)"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgms007">GMS-007</ref> "The Book of the Funeral Rite"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgms008">GMS-008</ref> "The Faith of the Fathers"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgms009">GMS-009</ref> "The Book of the Chants"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgms010">GMS-010</ref> "Missal"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgms011">GMS-011</ref> "Homily of the Saviour of the World"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgms012">GMS-012</ref> "The Book of the Funeral Rite"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgms013">GMS-013</ref> "Miracles of Mary"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgms014">GMS-014</ref> "Homily of St. Michael"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgms015">GMS-015</ref> "Synoptic Lectionary for the Year"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgms016">GMS-016</ref> "Vita of Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgms017">GMS-017</ref> "The Book of the Matrimony Rite"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgms018">GMS-018</ref> "Prayer of Mary"</ab>
         
